@{b}   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       memory = PA_AllocVecPooled( poolHeader, memSize )
       D0                          A0          D0

       @{"APTR" Link "INCLUDE:exec/types.h/Main" 33} PA_AllocVecPooled( @{"APTR" Link "INCLUDE:exec/types.h/Main" 33}, ULONG )

@{b}   FUNCTION@{ub}
       Allocates a memory block from a pool, and remembers the size of
       the block.  This function is identical to @{"PA_AllocPooled()" Link "PA_AllocPooled()"},
       except the size of the block is remembered for when it is later
       freed.  @{"PA_FreeVecPooled()" Link "PA_FreeVecPooled()"} must be used to free the block.

@{b}   INPUTS@{ub}
       poolHeader - ( @{"APTR" Link "INCLUDE:exec/types.h/Main" 33} ) The pool to allocate in.
       memSize    - ( ULONG ) Size of the block to allocate.

@{b}   RESULT@{ub}
       memory - ( @{"APTR" Link "INCLUDE:exec/types.h/Main" 33} ) A new block of memory, or NULL.

@{b}   TAGS@{ub}


@{b}   EXAMPLE@{ub}


@{b}   NOTES@{ub}
       .

@{b}   BUGS@{ub}
       .

@{b}   SEE ALSO@{ub}
       @{"PA_FreeVecPooled()" Link "PA_FreeVecPooled()"}, @{"PA_CreatePool()" Link "PA_CreatePool()"}, @{"PA_DeletePool()" Link "PA_DeletePool()"}

@EndNode

